<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;font-variant:normal;margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49pt;text-indent:-49pt;"><b>Item 2.02</b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;<b>Results of Operations and Financial Condition.</b></div>

<div style="font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:10pt;font-variant:normal;margin:0pt;">&#xa0;</div>

<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;font-variant:normal;margin:0pt;text-indent:25pt;">On April 5, 2023, Conagra Brands, Inc. (the &#8220;Company&#8221;) issued a press release which contained information on the Company&#8217;s&#xa0;third quarter fiscal&#xa0;2023 financial results. The press release is furnished with this Current Report on Form 8-K as Exhibit 99.1.</div>

<div style="font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:10pt;font-variant:normal;margin:0pt;">&#xa0;</div>

<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;font-variant:normal;margin:0pt;text-indent:25pt;">The information furnished pursuant to Item 2.02 of this Current Report on Form 8-K, including Exhibit 99.1, shall not be deemed &#8220;filed&#8221; for purposes of Section 18 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended (the &#8220;Exchange Act&#8221;), or otherwise subject to liabilities under that section and shall not be deemed to be incorporated by reference into any document filed under the Securities Act of 1933, as amended, or the Exchange Act, whether made before or after the date hereof, regardless of any general incorporation language in such filing.</div>

<div style="font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:10pt;font-variant:normal;margin:0pt;">&#xa0;</div>

<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:12pt;font-variant:normal;text-align:center;margin:0pt;"><font style="text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 12pt;"><b>CONAGRA BRANDS REPORTS <a data-tblloc="66x1" data-tblname="263810" data-tblv="9" id="led263810F2022681657299890245">third</a> QUARTER RESULTS</b></font></p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:10pt;font-variant:normal;margin:0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">CHICAGO,&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="23x1" data-tblname="263812" data-tblv="9" id="led263812F202210161668633717688">April 5, 2023</a> &#8212; Today Conagra Brands, Inc. (NYSE: CAG) reported results for the&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="66x1" data-tblname="263810" data-tblv="9" id="led263810F2022681657299913540">third</a> quarter of fiscal year <a data-tblloc="40x1" data-tblname="263810" data-tblv="9" id="led263810F2022681657300438393">2023</a>, which ended on <a data-tblloc="3x1" data-tblname="263812" data-tblv="9" id="led263812F2022681657300060254">February 26, 2023</a>. All comparisons are against the prior-year fiscal period, unless otherwise noted.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin: 0pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin: 0pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt;"><b><u>CEO Perspective</u></b></p>

<p style="margin: 0pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">Sean Connolly, president and chief executive officer of Conagra Brands, commented, "We delivered another quarter of strong results&nbsp;reflecting the ongoing strength of our brands and successful execution of the Conagra Way playbook. Our top-line posted solid growth as we demonstrated strong pricing execution with modest elasticities. Additionally, our productivity and service level improvement allowed us to continue to make meaningful progress on our adjusted gross margin and adjusted operating margin recovery, despite more&nbsp;impactful supply chain disruptions than anticipated. In response to our continued business momentum and ongoing operating dynamics, </font>we are&nbsp;raising our fiscal 2023 EPS&nbsp;guidance and narrowing our ranges for organic net sales growth and&nbsp;adjusted operating margin<font style="color:#000000;">. We remain committed to executing on our strategic business priorities including&nbsp;generating value for our shareholders."</font></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>Total Company&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="53x1" data-tblname="263810" data-tblv="9" id="led263810F2022681657299993307">Third Quarter</a> Results</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">In the quarter, net sales <a data-tblloc="2x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F2022781659986290835">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F2022791660049148270">5.9%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x1" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F2022791660049165813">$3.1</a> billion. The&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x7" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F2022791660049183268">increase</a> in net sales primarily reflects:</p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width: 100%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt;">

		<tr style="font-size: 11pt;">
			<td style="width: 18pt; font-size: 11pt;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; width: 18pt; font-size: 11pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&#9679;</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; font-size: 11pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">a&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="6x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F2022791660049248360">0.2%</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="6x7" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F2022791660049261993">decrease</a> from the unfavorable impact of foreign exchange; and</p>
			</td>
		</tr>

</table>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width: 100%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt;">

		<tr style="font-size: 11pt;">
			<td style="width: 18pt; font-size: 11pt;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; width: 18pt; font-size: 11pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&#9679;</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; font-size: 11pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">a&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F2022791660049282727">6.1%</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x7" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F2022791660049309446">increase</a> in organic net sales.</p>
			</td>
		</tr>

</table>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">The&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F2022791660049334186">6.1%</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x7" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F2022791660049359561">increase</a> in organic net sales was driven by a&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="9x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F2022791660049379536">15.1%</a> improvement in price/mix, which was partially offset by a&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="8x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F2022791660049390922">9.0%</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="8x7" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F2022791660049403285">decrease</a> in volume. Price/mix was driven by the company&#8217;s inflation-driven pricing actions.&nbsp;The volume decrease was primarily driven by the elasticity impact from inflation-driven pricing actions and supply chain, including manufacturing&nbsp;disruptions.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<div class="hf-row">
<div class="hf-cell TOCLink"><b>CONAGRA BRANDS</b></div>
</div>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 11pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left;"><b>Page 2</b></p>

<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Gross profit&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x5" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660049499647">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660049508835">20.3%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660049519257">$839</a> million in the quarter, and adjusted gross profit&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x5" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660049823859">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660049833892">23.9%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660049842458">$869</a> million.&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="55x1" data-tblname="263810" data-tblv="9" id="led263810F2022681657300031982">Third quarter</a> gross profit benefited from higher organic net sales and productivity,&nbsp;which more than offset the negative impacts of cost of goods sold inflation (including unfavorable commodity positions) and unfavorable operating leverage.&nbsp;Gross margin&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="5x5" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660049875311">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="5x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660049885768">325</a> basis points to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="4x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660049898776">27.2%</a> in the quarter, and adjusted gross margin&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="7x5" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660049914074">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="7x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660049924191">409</a> basis points to <a data-tblloc="6x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660049932524">28.1%</a>.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Selling, general, and administrative expense (SG&amp;A), which includes advertising and promotional expense (A&amp;P),&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="8x5" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660049962754">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="8x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660049972518">3.2%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="8x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660049981591">$349</a> million in the qu<font style="color:#333333;">arter and a</font>djusted SG&amp;A, which excludes A&amp;P,&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="9x5" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660049996959">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="9x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660050005761">12.4%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="9x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660050019689">$266</a> million driven b<font style="color:#333333;">y increased incentive compensation&nbsp;compared to&nbsp;the prior year quarter.</font></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">A&amp;P for the quarter increased&nbsp;</font><a data-tblloc="10x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F202211141671047348412">23.9%</a><font style="color:#000000;"> to&nbsp;</font><a data-tblloc="10x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660050063043">$81</a><font style="color:#000000;"> million, driven primarily by increased investment in modern marketing, including social and digital platforms.&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Net interest expense was&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x1" data-tblname="263814" data-tblv="9" id="led263814F2022791660050151152">$104</a> million in the quarter. Compared to the prior-year period, net interest expense&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x6" data-tblname="263814" data-tblv="9" id="led263814F2022791660050170543">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x5" data-tblname="263814" data-tblv="9" id="led263814F2022791660050179416">10.3%</a> or&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x3" data-tblname="263814" data-tblv="9" id="led263814F2022791660050187647">$10</a> m<font style="color:#333333;">illion, primarily due to a higher weighted average interest rate on outstanding debt.</font></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">The average diluted share count in the quarter was&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x1" data-tblname="263814" data-tblv="9" id="led263814F2022791660050327584">479</a> million shares.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 11pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left;">In the quarter, net income attributable to Conagra Brands increased&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="11x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F20232241679660641616">56.4%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="11x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660050393587">$342</a> million, or&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="13x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660050408870">$0.71</a> per diluted share. Adjusted net income attributable to Conagra Brands&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="12x5" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660050427061">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="12x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660051208036">31.3%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="12x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660051216702">$366</a> million, or&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="14x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F2022791660051225596">$0.76</a> per diluted share. The increase was&nbsp;driven primarily by the increase in gross profit.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Adjusted EBITDA, which includes equity method investment earnings and pension and postretirement non-service income,&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x5" data-tblname="263861" data-tblv="9" id="led263861F2022791660051274036">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x4" data-tblname="263861" data-tblv="9" id="led263861F2022791660051283076">21.1%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x1" data-tblname="263861" data-tblv="9" id="led263861F2022791660051294195">$669</a> million in the quarter, primarily driven by the increase&nbsp;in adjusted gross profit,&nbsp;slightly offset by lower pension income.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>Grocery &amp; Snacks Segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="53x1" data-tblname="263810" data-tblv="9" id="led263810F2022681657299999539">Third Quarter</a> Results</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Reported and organic net sales for the Grocery &amp; Snacks segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="10x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F2022791660051335237">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="10x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F2022791660051343571">3.7%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="10x1" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F2022791660051355324">$1.2</a> billion in the quarter.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">In the quarter, price/mix&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="14x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20227181660834514519">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="14x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20227181660834530115">13.7%</a> and volume&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="13x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20227181660834548261">decreased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="13x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20227181660834559215">10.0%</a>. Price/mix was driven by favorability in inflation-driven pricing. The volume decrease was primarily driven by the elasticity impact from inflation-driven pricing actions and&nbsp;shortages from supply chain disruptions.&nbsp;In the q<font style="color:#333333;">uarter, the company gained share in snacking categories including meat snacks and microwave popcorn, and some staples categories including refried beans&nbsp;and Asian sauces and marinades.</font></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Operating profit for the segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x6" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835300580">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x4" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835314034">10.8%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835328717">$256</a> million in the quarter. Adjusted operating profit&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x6" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835351847">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x4" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835364347">8.0%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835378757">$257</a> million&nbsp;as higher organic net sales and productivity more than offset the negative impacts of cost of goods sold inflation (including unfavorable commodity positions),&nbsp;continued elevated supply chain costs, and&nbsp;increased A&amp;P and SG&amp;A.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>Refrigerated &amp; Frozen Segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="53x1" data-tblname="263810" data-tblv="9" id="led263810F2022681657300003588">Third Quarter</a> Results</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Reported and organic net sales for the Refrigerated &amp; Frozen segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="15x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20228131663088117935">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="15x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20228131663088127664">5.6%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="15x1" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20228131663088149020">$1.3</a> billion in the quarter.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">In the quarter, price mix&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="19x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20227181660845796630">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="19x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20227181660845814175">15.4%</a> and volume&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="18x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20227181660845828718">decreased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="18x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20227181660845838199">9.8%</a>. Price/mix was driven by favorability in inflation-driven pricing. The volume decrease was primarily driven by the elasticity impact from inflation-driven pricing actions and&nbsp;shortages from supply chain disruptions.&nbsp;<font style="color:#333333;">In the quarter, the company gained share in categories such as frozen sides, plant-based protein, and frozen breakfast sausage.</font></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Operating profit for the segment <a data-tblloc="4x6" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F202211141671026690417">increased</a><font style="color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><a data-tblloc="4x4" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F202211141671026710449">66.9%</a><font style="color:#000000;"> to</font>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="4x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835426566">$264</a> million in the quarter. Adjusted operating profit&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="5x6" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835439908">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="5x4" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835449131">53.8%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="5x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835460673">$271</a> million as higher organic net sales and productivity more than offset the negative impacts of cost of goods sold inflation&nbsp;(including unfavorable commodity positions), unfavorable operating leverage, and increased A&amp;P and SG&amp;A.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>International Segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="53x1" data-tblname="263810" data-tblv="9" id="led263810F2022681657300008689">Third Quarter</a> Results</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Net sales for the International segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="20x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20228131663087917870">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="20x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20228131663087940696">7.7%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="20x1" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20228131663087957030">$260</a> million in the quarter reflecting:</p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width: 100%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt;">

		<tr style="font-size: 11pt;">
			<td style="width: 18pt; font-size: 11pt;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; width: 18pt; font-size: 11pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&#9679;</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; font-size: 11pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">a&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="22x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20228131663087990863">1.8%</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="22x7" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20228131663088041710">decrease</a> from the unfavorable impact of foreign exchange; and</p>
			</td>
		</tr>

</table>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width: 100%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt;">

		<tr style="font-size: 11pt;">
			<td style="width: 18pt; font-size: 11pt;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; width: 18pt; font-size: 11pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&#9679;</p>
			</td>
			<td style="vertical-align: top; font-size: 11pt;">
			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">a&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="21x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20228131663088009216">9.5%</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="21x7" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20228131663088025049">increase</a> in organic net sales.</p>
			</td>
		</tr>

</table>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">On an organic net sales basis, price/mix&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="25x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20227181660845865062">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="25x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20227181660845876742">16.5%</a> and volume&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="24x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20227181660845890712">decreased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="24x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20227181660845906102">7.0%</a>. Price/mix was driven by inflation-driven pricing. The volume decrease was primarily a result of the elasticity impact from inflation-driven pricing actions.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Operating profit for the segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="6x6" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835480363">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="6x4" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835491457">24.3%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="6x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835507368">$37</a> million in the quarter. Adjusted operating profit&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="7x6" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835520838">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="7x4" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835529870">23.9%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="7x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835541056">$37</a> million as the benefits from higher organic net sales and&nbsp;productivity&nbsp;were&nbsp;more than offset by the negative impact&nbsp;of cost of goods sold inflation (including unfavorable commodity positions),&nbsp;unfavorable operating leverage and continued elevated supply chain costs.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>Foodservice Segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="53x1" data-tblname="263810" data-tblv="9" id="led263810F2022681657300012778">Third Quarter</a> Results</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Reported and organic net sales for the Foodservice segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="26x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20227181660845944550">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="26x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20227181660845955102">17.3%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="26x1" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20227181660845972046">$275</a> million in the quarter.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">In the quarter, price/mix increased&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="30x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20227181660846051858">18.5%</a>&nbsp;and volume&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="29x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20227181660846017711">decreased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="29x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="9" id="led263825F20227181660846029439">1.2%</a>. Price/mix was driven by&nbsp;inflation-driven pricing. The volume decline was primarily a result of the elasticity impact from inflation-driven pricing actions.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Operating profit for the segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="8x6" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835558773">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="8x4" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835567800">409.6%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="8x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835595723">$24</a> million and adjusted operating profit&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="9x6" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835613611">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="9x4" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835622376">69.7%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="9x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20227181660835631690">$25</a> million in the quarter as the benefits of higher organic net sales and productivity more than offset the impacts of cost of goods sold inflation (including unfavorable commodity positions)&nbsp;and unfavorable operating leverage.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>Other&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="53x1" data-tblname="263810" data-tblv="9" id="led263810F2022681657300016886">Third Quarter</a> Items</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Corporate expenses&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="10x6" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20228131663089724781">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="10x4" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20228131663089737077">40.3%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="10x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20228131663089748565">$91</a> million in the qua<font style="color:#333333;">rter and adjuste</font>d corporate expense&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="11x6" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20228131663089764461">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="11x4" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20228131663089773144">14.3%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="11x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="9" id="led263837F20228131663089783848">$68</a> million in the<font style="color:#333333;"> quarter driven by increased incentive compensation compared to&nbsp;the prior year quarter.</font></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Pension and post-retirement non-service income was&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="9x1" data-tblname="263814" data-tblv="9" id="led263814F20227181660846326307">$6</a> million in the quarter compared to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="9x2" data-tblname="263814" data-tblv="9" id="led263814F20227181660846339340">$16</a> million of income in the prior-year period.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">In the quarter, equity method investment earnings were&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="10x1" data-tblname="263814" data-tblv="9" id="led263814F20227181660846351987">$51</a> million driven by continued favorable market conditions for the Ardent Mills joint venture, and the venture's effective management through recent volatility in the wheat markets.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">In the quarter, the effective tax rate was&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="19x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F20227181660846611717">22.6%</a> compared to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="19x2" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F20227181660846626747">33.4%</a> in the prior-year period. The adjusted effective tax rate was&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="20x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F20227181660846645523">22.8%</a> compared to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="20x2" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="9" id="led263848F20227181660846654756">24.4%</a> in the prior-year period.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">In the quarter, the company<font style="color:#333333;"> paid a dividend of $0.33 per share.&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 8pt; text-indent: -9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Please note that certain prior year amounts have been reclassified to conform with current year presentation.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>Discussion of Results</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Conagra Brands will host a webcast and conference call at 9:30 a.m. Eastern time today to discuss the results. The live audio webcast and presentation slides will be available on <u>www.conagrabrands.com/investor-relations</u> under Events &amp; Presentations. The conference call may be accessed by dialing 1-877-883-0383 for participants in the U.S. and 1-412-902-6506 for all other participants and using passcode 2483233. Please dial in 10 to 15 minutes prior to the call start time. Following the company's remarks, the conference call will include a question-and-answer session with the investment community. A replay of the webcast will be available on www.conagrabrands.com/investor-relations under Events &amp; Presentations until April 5, 2024.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>About Conagra Brands</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Conagra Brands, Inc. (NYSE: CAG), headquartered in Chicago, is one of North America's leading branded food companies. Guided by an entrepreneurial spirit, Conagra Brands combines a rich heritage of making great food with a sharpened focus on innovation. The company's portfolio is evolving to satisfy people's changing food preferences. Conagra's iconic brands, such as Birds Eye&#174;, Duncan Hines&#174;, Healthy Choice&#174;, Marie&nbsp;Callender's&#174;, Reddi-wip&#174;, and&nbsp;Slim Jim&#174;, as well as emerging brands, including Angie's&#174; BOOMCHICKAPOP&#174;, Duke's&#174;, Earth Balance&#174;, Gardein&#174;, and Frontera&#174;, offer choices for every occasion. For more information, visit <u>www.conagrabrands.com</u>.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>Note on Forward-Looking Statements</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">This document contains forward-looking statements within the meaning of the federal securities laws. These forward-looking statements are based on management's current expectations and are subject to uncertainty and changes in circumstances. Readers of this document should understand that these statements are not guarantees of performance or results. Many factors could affect our actual financial results and cause them to vary materially from the expectations contained in the forward-looking statements, including those set forth in this document. These risks, uncertainties, and factors include, among other things: the risk that the cost savings and any other synergies from the acquisition of Pinnacle Foods Inc. (the Pinnacle acquisition) may not be fully realized or may take longer to realize than expected; the risk that the Pinnacle acquisition may not be accretive within the expected timeframe or to the extent anticipated; the risks that the Pinnacle acquisition and related integration will create disruption to the company and its management and impede the achievement of business plans; risks related to our ability to achieve the intended benefits of other recent acquisitions and divestitures; risks associated with general economic and industry conditions; risks associated with our ability to successfully execute our long-term value creation strategies; risks related to our ability to deleverage on currently anticipated timelines, and to continue to access capital on acceptable terms or at all; risks related to our ability to execute operating and restructuring plans and achieve targeted operating efficiencies from cost-saving initiatives, and to benefit from trade optimization programs; risks related to the effectiveness of our hedging activities and ability to respond to volatility in commodities; risks related to the company's competitive environment and related market conditions; risks related to our ability to respond to changing consumer preferences and the success of our innovation and marketing investments; risks related to the ultimate impact of any product recalls and litigation, including litigation related to the lead-based paint and pigment matters, as well as any securities litigation, including securities class action lawsuits; risk associated with actions of governments and regulatory bodies that affect our businesses, including the ultimate impact of new or revised regulations or interpretations; risks related to the impact of the COVID-19 pandemic on our business, suppliers, consumers, customers and employees; risks related to our forecasts of consumer eat-at-home habits as the impacts of the COVID-19 pandemic abate; risks related to the availability and prices of supply chain resources, including raw materials, packaging, and transportation including any negative effects caused by changes in inflation rates, weather conditions, health pandemics or outbreaks of disease, actual or threatened hostilities or war, or other geopolitical uncertainty; disruptions or inefficiencies in our supply chain and/or operations, including from the COVID-19 pandemic; risks related to disruptions in the global economy caused by the ongoing conflict between Russia and Ukraine; risks associated with actions by our customers, including changes in distribution and purchasing terms; risks and uncertainties associated with intangible assets, including any future goodwill or intangible assets impairment charges; risks related to a material failure in or breach of our or our vendors&#8217; information technology systems; the amount and timing of future dividends, which remain subject to Board approval and depend on market and other conditions; risks related to the company's ability to execute on its strategies or achieve expectations related to environmental, social, and governance matters, including as a result of evolving legal, regulatory, and other standards, processes, and assumptions, the pace of scientific and technological developments, increased costs, the availability of requisite financing, and changes in carbon</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>Note on Non-GAAP Financial Measures</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">This document includes certain non-GAAP financial measures, including adjusted EPS, organic net sales, adjusted gross profit, adjusted operating profit, adjusted SG&amp;A, adjusted corporate expenses, adjusted gross margin, adjusted operating margin, adjusted effective tax rate, adjusted net income attributable to Conagra Brands, free cash flow, net debt, net leverage ratio, and adjusted EBITDA. Management considers GAAP financial measures as well as such non-GAAP financial information in its evaluation of the company&#8217;s financial statements and believes these non-GAAP financial measures provide useful supplemental information to assess the company&#8217;s operating performance and financial position. These measures should be viewed in addition to, and not in lieu of, the company&#8217;s diluted earnings per share, operating performance and financial measures as calculated in accordance with GAAP.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Organic net sales excludes, from reported net sales, the impacts of foreign exchange, divested businesses and acquisitions, as well as the impact of any 53<sup style="vertical-align:top;line-height:120%;font-size:pt">rd</sup> week. All references to changes in volume and price/mix throughout this release are on an organic net sales basis.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">References to adjusted items throughout this release refer to measures computed in accordance with GAAP less the impact of items impacting comparability. Items impacting comparability are income or expenses (and related tax impacts) that management believes have had, or are likely to have, a significant impact on the earnings of the applicable business segment or on the total corporation for the period in which the item is recognized, and are not indicative of the company&#8217;s core operating results. These items thus affect the comparability of underlying results from period to period.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">References to earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation, and amortization (EBITDA) refer to net income attributable to Conagra Brands before the impacts of discontinued operations, income tax expense (benefit), interest expense, depreciation, and amortization. References to adjusted EBITDA refer to EBITDA before the impacts of items impacting comparability.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Hedge gains and losses are generally aggregated, and net amounts are reclassified from unallocated corporate expense to the operating segments when the underlying commodity or foreign currency being hedged is expensed in segment cost of goods sold. The net change in the derivative gains (losses) included in unallocated corporate expense during the period is reflected as a comparability item, Corporate hedging derivate gains (losses).</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>Note on Forward-Looking&nbsp;Non-GAAP Financial Measures</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Our fiscal 2023 guidance includes certain non-GAAP financial measures (organic net sales growth, adjusted operating margin, adjusted EPS, net leverage ratio, and adjusted effective tax rate) that are presented on a forward-looking basis. Historically, the company has calculated these non-GAAP financial measures excluding the impact of certain items such as, but not limited to, foreign exchange, acquisitions, divestitures, restructuring expenses, the extinguishment of debt, hedging gains and losses, impairment charges, legacy legal contingencies, and unusual tax items. Reconciliations of these forward-looking non-GAAP financial measures to the most directly comparable GAAP financial measures are not provided because the company is unable to provide such reconciliations without unreasonable effort, due to the uncertainty and inherent difficulty of predicting the timing and financial impact of such items. For the same reasons, the company is unable to address the probable significance of the unavailable information, which could be material to future results.</p>

<p style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 8pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><sup style="vertical-align:top;line-height:120%;font-size:pt">1 </sup>Operating profit is derived from taking Income from continuing operations before income taxes and equity method investment earnings, adding back Interest expense, net and removing Pension and postretirement non-service income.</p>

<p style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 8pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><sup style="vertical-align:top;line-height:120%;font-size:pt">2</sup> Advertising and promotion expense (A&amp;P) has been removed from adjusted selling, general and administrative expense because this metric is used in reporting to management, and management believes this adjusted measure provides useful supplemental information to assess the company&#8217;s operating performance.&nbsp; Please note that A&amp;P is not removed from adjusted profit measures.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:10pt;font-variant:normal;margin:0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 8pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><sup style="vertical-align:top;line-height:120%;font-size:pt">1 </sup>Operating profit is derived from taking Income from continuing operations before income taxes and equity method investment earnings, adding back Interest expense, net and removing Pension and postretirement non-service income.</p>

<p style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 8pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><sup style="vertical-align:top;line-height:120%;font-size:pt">2</sup> Advertising and promotion expense (A&amp;P) has been removed from adjusted selling, general and administrative expense because this metric is used in reporting to management, and management believes this adjusted measure provides useful supplemental information to assess the company&#8217;s operating performance.&nbsp; Please note that A&amp;P is not removed from adjusted profit measures.</p>

// Edgar(tm) Renderer was created by staff of the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission.  Data and content created by government employees within the scope of their employment are not subject to domestic copyright protection. 17 U.S.C. 105.
var Show={};Show.LastAR=null,Show.showAR=function(a,r,w){if(Show.LastAR)Show.hideAR();var e=a;while(e&&e.nodeName!='TABLE')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e||e.nodeName!='TABLE'){var ref=((window)?w.document:document).getElementById(r);if(ref){e=ref.cloneNode(!0);
e.removeAttribute('id');a.parentNode.appendChild(e)}}
if(e)e.style.display='block';Show.LastAR=e};Show.hideAR=function(){Show.LastAR.style.display='none'};Show.toggleNext=function(a){var e=a;while(e.nodeName!='DIV')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e.style){}else if(!e.style.display){}else{var d,p_;if(e.style.display=='none'){d='block';p='-'}else{d='none';p='+'}
e.style.display=d;if(a.textContent){a.textContent=p+a.textContent.substring(1)}else{a.innerText=p+a.innerText.substring(1)}}}

/* Updated 2009-11-04 */
